Preheat your oven to 220°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of
@salt{}. Halve the @yellow pepper{1}, remove the core and seeds and thinly slice. Peel and
grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the pepper slices on a #baking
tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{} and @ground black
pepper{}. Toss to coat then roast on the middle shelf of your oven until charred and soft,
~{12-14%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the oven and set aside.

Meanwhile, add the @wholewheat penne{176%g} to the pan of boiling water and simmer until
tender, ~{13-14%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan and
drizzle with @olive oil{} to stop it sticking together.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the garlic. Fry
the garlic for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%can}.
Add the @vegetable stock powder{1}, @water{100%ml}(for the sauce), a pinch of @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Add a pinch of @chilli flakes{1/4%tsp}
(only a small pinch, they're hot and you can add more later if you want!). Simmer the sauce
until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @olives{30} and add them to the simmering sauce. Roughly chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1}(stalks and all), set aside. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and
pop them in a large #bowl{}. Add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and a glug of @olive oil{}
along with a pinch of @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add the @walnuts{20}, toss to
coat, then leave to the side.

Once the yellow pepper is cooked, add it to the sauce. When the sauce has finished cooking,
taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Add the cooked wholewheat penne to
the sauce (or add the sauce to the pan with the wholewheat penne if that's easier!) along
with half the parsley, and stir to combine together. Taste and add another small pinch of
chilli flakes if you like things spicy (remember, they do pack a punch!).

Add the @wild rocket{40} to the bowl with the tomatoes and toss together to coat the leaves
in the dressing. Serve the wholewheat pasta in #bowls{} with the salad alongside. Sprinkle
the remaining parsley over the wheat pasta. Enjoy!